<br>
Druids get a spell series like it so that there could be more than one class capable of porting people around, and to have additional port locations under the condidtion that it be with a druid instead of a wizard.<br>
<br>
While there might be some small balance issue with us having tracking, there is also the great utility value of it.  In general, on luclin at least, there is not a huge population of rangers, certainly not overflowing with them.  And while there certainly seem to be plenty of druids, its generally better to avoid having them pull.  <br>
That leaves the mid-high level bard population and any ranger you can find.  <br>
<br>
I don't think us having track would unbalance this, and I think there is one more special utility.  Luclin is still pretty empty, at least on the Luclin server.  Aside from the Nexus, and Shadow haven, few zones spot over 20 people ever unless they are really large raids.  Well as there are many vah shir beast lords only too happy to hunt near their homelands and trainers, these beastlords, and any traveling beastlords in search of much of the semi decent loot on the moon could act as trackers for their groups. Having a tracker frequently might make luclin more appealing, and help fill out those zones.  Not to mention it would enable people searching for Twilight Sea items able to find a tracker fairly easily in order to accomplish the task.<br>
<br>
